              "body": "Team,\n\nFred and I met last week to discuss areas for improvement in our forecasting process. I plan to meet with Tom this week to review a few ideas, after which Fred and I will regroup and prepare recommendations for the broader team.\n\nIn the meantime, if you’d like to explore different forecasting approaches, here is a useful blog post: 12 proven sales forecasting methods to predict revenue | Outreach\n\nThank you,\nMA\n\nMarc Alex Forget\n\nSenior Vice-President of Sales and Marketing | Vice‑président principal, Ventes et Marketing\n\n437-500-2700\naptum.com | LinkedIn\n\nFrom: Frederic Gingras <Frederic.Gingras@aptum.com>\nSent: Tuesday, February 24, 2026 8:19 PM\nTo: Ian Rae <Ian.Rae@aptum.com>; Sarah Blanchard <Sarah.Blanchard@aptum.com>; Adam Nelson <Adam.Nelson@aptum.com>; Marc Alex Forget <Marc-Alexandre.Forget@aptum.com>; Marc Pare <Marc.Pare@aptum.com>\nCc: Tom Kelsch <Tom.Kelsch@aptum.com>; Jorge Quintero <Jorge.Quintero@aptum.com>\nSubject: Thoughts on improving forecasting\n\nHi team,\n\nI've been thinking about our forecasting calls, how the forecast changes so much between the start and end of the month, and I've been collecting some thoughts around this. Keen to hear your thoughts...\n\n@Marc Alex Forget, the following may or may not apply in your case, as I understand that defining timelines with partners involved can be... complex... but keen to get your feedback on this.\n\nWe often see:\n\nOpportunities in wrong stages\n\nClose dates that are wrong\n\nDeals constantly slipping\n\nIssue ",
              "outlook_url": "https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGJlOTlmOWI5LTRkMjctNGVlOS04MTc2LWNhZjk3MGFiMWZkMABGAAAAAAD5B%2BzdKDBUQY8PUJDbFq%2F0BwBAscG%2BD3c%2FSI%2FxeA%2BiWIqgAAAAAAEMAABAscG%2BD3c%2FSI%2FxeA%2BiWIqgAARrT5OtAAA%3D&exvsurl=1&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem"
            }
          ]
